<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[100,771,1738,1982]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
The damselflies are recovered as monophyletic with high support. There has been some uncertainty about the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1854" box="[675,770,1796,1815]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" rank="subOrder" subOrder="Zygoptera">Zygoptera</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hasegawa, E. &amp; Kasuya, E." box="[108,385,1823,1842]" journalOrPublisher="Entomol. Sci." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="55 - 66" part="9" refId="ref17843" refString="Hasegawa, E., Kasuya, E., 2006. Phylogenetic analysis of the insect order Odonata using 28 S and 16 S rDNA sequences: a comparison between data sets with different evolutionary rates. Entomol. Sci. 9, 55 - 66." title="Phylogenetic analysis of the insect order Odonata using 28 S and 16 S rDNA sequences: a comparison between data sets with different evolutionary rates" type="journal article" year="2006">Hasegawa and Kasuya, 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Saux, C. &amp; Simon, C. &amp; Spicer, G. S." box="[396,561,1823,1842]" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Entomol. Soc. Am." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="693 - 699" part="96" refId="ref19984" refString="Saux, C., Simon, C., Spicer, G. S., 2003. Phylogeny of the dragonfly and damselfly order Odonata as inferred by mitochondrial 12 S ribosomal RNA sequences. Ann. Entomol. Soc. Am. 96, 693 - 699." title="Phylogeny of the dragonfly and damselfly order Odonata as inferred by mitochondrial 12 S ribosomal RNA sequences" type="journal article" year="2003">Saux et al., 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Trueman, J. W. H." box="[573,719,1823,1842]" journalOrPublisher="Odonatologica" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="59 - 72" part="25" refId="ref20383" refString="Trueman, J. W. H., 1996. A preliminary cladistic analysis of odonate wing venation. Odonatologica 25, 59 - 72." title="A preliminary cladistic analysis of odonate wing venation" type="journal article" year="1996">Trueman, 1996</bibRefCitation>
) and particularly the relationship of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Calvert" authorityYear="1901" box="[416,505,1851,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Lestoideidae" genus="Lestoidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lestoidea</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[547,648,1851,1870]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Anisoptera" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Anisoptera</taxonomicName>
in the past (
<bibRefCitation author="Hasegawa, E. &amp; Kasuya, E." box="[108,382,1879,1898]" journalOrPublisher="Entomol. Sci." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="55 - 66" part="9" refId="ref17843" refString="Hasegawa, E., Kasuya, E., 2006. Phylogenetic analysis of the insect order Odonata using 28 S and 16 S rDNA sequences: a comparison between data sets with different evolutionary rates. Entomol. Sci. 9, 55 - 66." title="Phylogenetic analysis of the insect order Odonata using 28 S and 16 S rDNA sequences: a comparison between data sets with different evolutionary rates" type="journal article" year="2006">Hasegawa and Kasuya, 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Saux, C. &amp; Simon, C. &amp; Spicer, G. S." box="[393,554,1879,1898]" journalOrPublisher="Ann. Entomol. Soc. Am." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="693 - 699" part="96" refId="ref19984" refString="Saux, C., Simon, C., Spicer, G. S., 2003. Phylogeny of the dragonfly and damselfly order Odonata as inferred by mitochondrial 12 S ribosomal RNA sequences. Ann. Entomol. Soc. Am. 96, 693 - 699." title="Phylogeny of the dragonfly and damselfly order Odonata as inferred by mitochondrial 12 S ribosomal RNA sequences" type="journal article" year="2003">Saux et al., 2003</bibRefCitation>
), but it is clear due to high support from both these data and all other recent molecular analyses (
<bibRefCitation author="Bybee, S. M. &amp; Ogden, T. H. &amp; Branham, M. A. &amp; Whiting, M. F." box="[159,328,1935,1954]" journalOrPublisher="Cladistics" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="477 - 514" part="24" refId="ref16610" refString="Bybee, S. M., Ogden, T. H., Branham, M. A., Whiting, M. F., 2008. Molecules, morphology and fossils: a comprehensive approach to odonate phylogeny and the evolution of the odonate wing. Cladistics 24, 477 - 514." title="Molecules, morphology and fossils: a comprehensive approach to odonate phylogeny and the evolution of the odonate wing" type="journal article" year="2008">Bybee et al., 2008</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dumont, H. J. &amp; Vierstraete, A. &amp; Vanfleteren, J. R." box="[337,526,1935,1954]" journalOrPublisher="Syst. Entomol." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="6 - 18" part="35" refId="ref17305" refString="Dumont, H. J., Vierstraete, A., Vanfleteren, J. R., 2010. A molecular phylogeny of the Odonata (Insecta). Syst. Entomol. 35, 6 - 18." title="A molecular phylogeny of the Odonata (Insecta)" type="journal article" year="2010">Dumont et al., 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dijkstra, K. - D. - B. &amp; Kalkman, V. J. &amp; Dow, R. A. &amp; Stokvis, F. R. &amp; Van Tol, J. A. N." box="[535,719,1935,1954]" journalOrPublisher="Syst. Entomol." pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="68 - 96" part="39" refId="ref17175" refString="Dijkstra, K. - D. - B., Kalkman, V. J., Dow, R. A., Stokvis, F. R., Van Tol, J. A. N., 2014. Redefining the damselfly families: a comprehensive molecular phylogeny of Z ygoptera (O donata). Syst. Entomol. 39, 68 - 96." title="Redefining the damselfly families: a comprehensive molecular phylogeny of Z ygoptera (O donata)" type="journal article" year="2014">Dijkstra et al., 2014</bibRefCitation>
) that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys-Longchamps" authorityYear="1854" box="[100,195,1963,1982]" pageId="6" pageNumber="15" rank="subOrder" subOrder="Zygoptera">Zygoptera</taxonomicName>
is monophyletic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
